'''Helpless Automaton''' is the fifth song on the album [[Business As Usual]] by the popular Australian band [[Men at Work]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmguide.musicmatch.com/album/album.cgi?ALBUMID=442096|title=Business as Usual by Men at Work|publisher=Musicmatch Inc|accessdate=2007-10-11}}</ref> The song concerns a human who is infatuated with another human, but feels as though frigid, computer-like thoughts and emotions are hindering romantic progress. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sing365.com/music/Lyric.nsf/Helpless-Automaton-lyrics-Men-at-Work/FD04AF1A54FBEAC0482568BF00018845|title=Helpless Automaton Lyrics|publisher=Sing365.com|accessdate=2007-10-10}}</ref> It is the only song on the album written solely by the keyboard/flute/saxophone player [[Greg Ham]], who sings to song.<ref>{{cite web| title =Discography-Men at Work-Business as Usual| publisher =AEC One Stop Group Inc| url =http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?aid=11502&pid=5187| accessdate =2007-10-11}}</ref>  Helpless Automaton features a catchy beat and melody as well as a guitar solo at the end by guitarist [[Ron Strykert]].  The song, released in [[1982]], was never released as a single.<ref>{{cite web| last =Shelton| first =Sonya| title =Men at Work Biography| publisher =Net Industries| date =2007| url =http://www.musicianguide.com/biographies/1608003061/Men-at-Work.html| accessdate =2007-10-12  }}</ref>

